{"tid":738012,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[再召喚關囝] 吉隆坡輕鐵試行QR Code入閘","createTime":"2018-07-11T08:12:07.000Z","updateTime":"2018-07-16T07:22:46.000Z","uid":1159,"like":1,"dislike":5,"uniUserReply":5,"replies":[{"pid":"897a249204d3f84428356ae042a47c538f950f59","tid":738012,"uid":1159,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-11T08:12:07.000Z","msg":"<strong>Touch N Go Will Let You Pay For LRT Rides With Your Smartphone</strong><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://www.soyacincau.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/180606-Touch-n-go-transit-QR-payment-0.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soyacincau.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F180606-Touch-n-go-transit-QR-payment-0.jpg&h=06c4bfca&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nThe physical Touch &lsquo;n Go card has been the defacto choice for commuters. You don&rsquo;t have to queue up to buy tokens and you get to enjoy the lower cashless fare.<br />\n<br />\nSoon, you&rsquo;ll be able to pay for your train rides with your smartphone as Touch &lsquo;n Go is rolling out a new feature starting this week.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://www.soyacincau.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/180606-Touch-n-go-transit-QR-payment.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soyacincau.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F180606-Touch-n-go-transit-QR-payment.jpg&h=3ec159bf&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nIt&rsquo;s reported that TNG Digital is enabling the Kelana Jaya LRT line to accept QR code payments using the Touch &lsquo;n Go app. In case you didn&rsquo;t know, the mobile wallet is completely different from the Touch &lsquo;n Go card and you&rsquo;ll need to reload it separately.<br />\n<br />\nAccording to Amanz, this form of mobile payment will be offered to 1,000 users in its initial testing phase. The trial run will start this week until 31 July 2018.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://www.soyacincau.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/180606-Touch-n-go-transit-QR-pay.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soyacincau.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F180606-Touch-n-go-transit-QR-pay.jpg&h=a7ca0502&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nWe are curious if QR-code based payments are actually more convenient than tapping a Touch &lsquo;n Go card. According to the slide above, you would need to present your QR code at gate. To do that in its current version, <strong>you&rsquo;ll need to launch the app, tap on pay and enter your 6-digit PIN before it displays the custom QR-code. That&rsquo;s quite a lot of steps needed before you walk up to the gate</strong>. If you&rsquo;ve tried the e-gate system at cinemas, you&rsquo;ll know that some users might struggle with QR-codes if the screen isn&rsquo;t bright enough.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>We still think that it could have been better if it was done via NFC. </strong>Hopefully the final product works better than the recently discontinued Touch &lsquo;n Go top-up feature. What do you guys think? Let us know in the comments below.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.soyacincau.com/2018/06/06/touch-n-go-will-let-you-pay-for-lrt-rides-with-your-smartphone/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.soyacincau.com%2F2018%2F06%2F06%2Ftouch-n-go-will-let-you-pay-for-lrt-rides-with-your-smartphone%2F&d=JTRu4UmWOKpqXX3Vlp%2FPAfiMucz1dB5Ms3PJ3VCnrF8%3D&h=6e2aec02\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.soyacincau.com/2018/06/06/touch-n-go-will-let-you-pay-for-lrt-rides-with-your-smartphone/</a>"},{"pid":"e3a4c8ecb31cbc91ec9d77d5ec50391d0db83ba9","tid":738012,"uid":47359,"like":7,"dislike":4,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-11T08:16:03.000Z","msg":"重未柒夠<br />\n<br />\n香港有payme, applepay, 八達通就夠。唔撚使we7支付寶<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://lihkg.com/t/672991/4?ref=android\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lihkg.com/t/672991/4?ref=android</a><br />\n<br />\nLIHKG @ Android"},{"pid":"77192e16555f27bbcdd166d8d2f33a26ee53055b","tid":7